.TH "NAVIGATEEVENT.NAVIGATEEVENT" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
NavigateEvent.NavigateEvent \- NavigateEvent: NavigateEvent()
constructor
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]NavigateEvent()\f[B]\f[R] constructor creates a new
\f[CR]NavigateEvent\f[R] object instance.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
new NavigateEvent(type, init)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]type\f[R]
A string representing the type of event.
.TP
\f[B]init\f[R]
An object that, \f[I]in addition to the properties defined in
\f[CI]Event()\f[I]\f[R], has the following properties:
.RS
.TP
\f[B]canIntercept\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
A boolean defining whether the navigation can be intercepted or not
(e.g., you can\(cqt intercept a cross\-origin navigation).
Defaults to \f[CR]false\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]destination\f[R]
A \f[CR]NavigationDestination\f[R] object representing the location
being navigated to.
.TP
\f[B]downloadRequest\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
The filename of the file requested for download, in the case of a
download navigation (e.g., an \f[CR]<a>\f[R] or \f[CR]<area>\f[R]
element with a \f[CR]download\f[R] attribute).
Defaults to \f[CR]null\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]formData\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
The \f[CR]FormData\f[R] object representing the submitted data in the
case of a \f[CR]POST\f[R] form submission.
Defaults to \f[CR]null\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]hashChange\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
A boolean defining if the navigation is a fragment navigation (i.e., to
a fragment identifier in the same document).
Defaults to \f[CR]false\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]hasUAVisualTransition\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
A boolean defining whether the user agent has performed a visual
transition for this navigation before dispatching this event.
Defaults to \f[CR]false\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]info\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
The \f[CR]info\f[R] data value passed by the initiating navigation
operation (e.g., \f[CR]Navigation.back()\f[R], or
\f[CR]Navigation.navigate()\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]navigationType\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
The type of the navigation.
Possible values \(em \f[CR]push\f[R], \f[CR]reload\f[R],
\f[CR]replace\f[R], and \f[CR]traverse\f[R].
Defaults to \f[CR]push\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]signal\f[R]
An \f[CR]AbortSignal\f[R], which will become aborted if the navigation
is cancelled (e.g., by the user pressing the browser\(cqs \(lqStop\(rq
button, or another navigation starting and thus cancelling the ongoing
one).
.TP
\f[B]sourceElement\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
An \f[CR]Element\f[R] object representing the initiating element in
cases where the navigation was initiated by an element, or
\f[CR]null\f[R] if the navigation was not initiated by an element.
Defaults to \f[CR]null\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]userInitiated\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
A boolean defining whether the navigation was initiated by the user
(e.g., by clicking a link, submitting a form, or pressing the
browser\(cqs \(lqBack\(rq/\(lqForward\(rq buttons).
Defaults to \f[CR]false\f[R].
.RE
.SS Return value
A new \f[CR]NavigateEvent\f[R] object.
.SH EXAMPLES
A developer would not use this constructor manually.
A new \f[CR]NavigateEvent\f[R] object is constructed when a handler is
invoked as a result of the \f[CR]navigate\f[R] event firing.
.IP
.EX
navigation.addEventListener(\(dqnavigate\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[I]// Exit early if this navigation shouldn\(aqt be intercepted,\f[R]
  \f[I]// e.g. if the navigation is cross\-origin, or a download request\f[R]
  \f[B]if\f[R] (shouldNotIntercept(event)) {
    \f[B]return\f[R];
  }

  \f[B]const\f[R] url = \f[B]new\f[R] URL(event.destination.url);

  \f[B]if\f[R] (url.pathname.startsWith(\(dq/articles/\(dq)) {
    event.intercept({
      \f[B]async\f[R] handler() {
        \f[I]// The URL has already changed, so show a placeholder while\f[R]
        \f[I]// fetching the new content, such as a spinner or loading page\f[R]
        renderArticlePagePlaceholder();

        \f[I]// Fetch the new content and display when ready\f[R]
        \f[B]const\f[R] articleContent = \f[B]await\f[R] getArticleContent(url.pathname);
        renderArticlePage(articleContent);
      },
    });
  }
});
.EE
